Step1: Create a new conda env
    conda create -n linearapp python==3.6.9
Step2:Install requirements.txt
    pip install - requirements.txt
Step3:Create a file named procfile
    there is o extension for this Procfile
    P should be capital
Step4:Initialize your project as git project
    git init
Step4:start tracking changes
    git status
Heroku commands:
(from chat)
# git init
# git add .
# git commit -m "initial commit"
# heroku create
# git remote -v
# git push heroku master
